TY  - JOUR
AU  - Bull, Clive
AU  - Jovanovic, Boyan
T1  - Mismatch Versus Derived-Demand Shift as Causes of Labour Mobility
PY  - 1988
Y1  - 1988/01/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297536
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 55
IS  - 1
SP  - 169
EP  - 175
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - Labour mobility may be caused by shifts in the derived demand for labour on the part of firms or sectors, or it may be caused by mismatches between workers and their jobs. Both reasons may be important, and this paper merges them into one model. It explores the consequences for (a) wage-tenure relationships and (b) the issue of sluggishness of wages caused by the implied selectivity of workers into preferred jobs and sectors.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297536
ER  - 



